data.title: Kapszukiewicz reelected mayor of Toledo
meta_keywords: Local government in the United States
data.meta_description: Toledo Mayor Wade Kapszukiewicz secured the continuation of his place in Toledo's mayoral seat on Election Day. Kapszukiewicz received 21,004 votes while his opponent, former Mayor Carty Finkbeiner, got 9,055, a68. 9% to29. 71% win. The mayor declared his victory ahead of official results Tuesday night at Earnest Brew Works, addressing his victories throughout his four years thus far including the Toledo Recovery Planandroad repairs while claiming a historic margin of victory.
data.text:
Toledo Mayor Wade Kapszukiewicz secured the continuation of his place in Toledo's mayoral seat on Election Day.

The mayor declared his victory ahead of official results Tuesday night at , addressing his victories throughout his four years thus far including the and while claiming a historic margin of victory.

"Tonight, by a record margin, Toledo is overwhelmingly voted to embrace that future and reject that past," Kapszukiewicz declared.

Before poll closures, Finkbeiner said he was grateful to have health to run again and the opportunity to go up against a great mayor, expressing that he is ready for anything that comes his way in the future.

"If I do end up short in the votes tonight, that that's going to alter my life, no, it isn't," Finkbeiner said. "You know what? Because in a week, two weeks, maybe in 30 days at the most, there's going to be somebody going, 'We got a problem. Would you be interested in helping us with that problem?'"
